    <h4>🕰 Classical: Active Shape Models (Cootes 1995)</h4>
    <p>Build a PCA model of valid landmark configurations. Fitting iteratively moves points toward local image gradients while constraining the shape to lie within ±3 standard deviations of the training distribution. Sensitive to initialisation and poor in profile views.</p>
    <h4>🤖 Neural: CNN Regression (used here)</h4>
    <p>A CNN trained end-to-end with MSE loss directly regresses all 68 (x,y) coordinates from a cropped face image. The vladmandic fork uses a small but accurate architecture achieving sub-pixel error on standard benchmarks at high speed in the browser.</p>
    <div class="hbox hb-g">📐 <strong>Affine alignment:</strong> Compute angle θ = atan2(Δy,Δx) between eye centres, rotate image by −θ, scale so inter-eye distance = 72 px. This is the single most important pre-processing step for recognition accuracy.</div>
