    <h4>Averaging Multiple Reference Descriptors</h4>
    <p>Averaging N descriptor vectors produces a centroid that is more stable than any single photo:</p>
    <div class="formula">d_avg = ‖ (1/N) · Σᵢ refᵢ − comp ‖₂</div>
    <p>This is <strong>nearest-centroid classification</strong> — one of the oldest and simplest classifiers in ML, yet highly effective when the embedding space is well-conditioned (as it is after triplet training).</p>
    <h4>Cosine Similarity (secondary metric shown)</h4>
    <div class="formula">cos(a,b) = (a · b) / (‖a‖ · ‖b‖)</div>
    <p>Scale-invariant; for unit-normalised vectors, cosine similarity = 1 − (d²/2), so the two metrics are equivalent up to monotone transformation.</p>
